article.headline: Marist 71, Rider 55
article.story: POUGHKEEPSIE, N.Y. (AP) -- Jared Jordan scored 13 points and passed out 11 assists, helping Marist to a 71-55 victory over Rider on Friday night. Shae McNamara came off the bench to score a game-high 14 points and Will Whittington contributed 12 points for Marist (11-4 overall, 3-1 MAAC), which never trailed. The Red Foxes bench outscored Rider's reserves, 24-8. Jason Thompson scored 13 points and pulled down a game-high 10 rebounds for Rider (8-6, 2-2). Harris Mansell and Terrance Mouton each scored 12 points in a losing effort. Rider shot 37.9 percent from the field, while Marist shot 47.5 percent.
